# PressThat

This project is called PressThat.

PressThat is a system tray app that connects to your WordPress website to create and view draft posts.

After first installing the app, you need to configure it with your website details. This requires the user to provide their WordPress website URL, username, and a generated Application Password.

Users can generate an Application Password in their WordPress dashboard at the bottom of the "Users -> Profile" page. This password is unique and can be easily revoked at any time.

## New user experience (NUX)

Here's a quick flow for how the new user experience (NUX) will work:

1. On first launch, show an onboarding/config screen (not the main tray UI).
2. Ask for WordPress site URL, username, and Application Password.
3. Validate credentials against the WordPress REST API before saving.
4. Persist credentials securely in the OS keychain / secure storage (never plain text in repo or logs).
5. After successful setup, open the system tray experience for creating/viewing draft posts.
6. Allow revisiting settings later to update or revoke connection details.
